Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before this court today to take full responsibility for my actions and plead guilty to the offense of affray. I acknowledge that my behavior at the bar was unacceptable and I deeply regret the fear and unease I caused to others present.

On that fateful day, I discovered that my boyfriend had betrayed my trust by cheating on me. Fueled by anger and hurt, I impulsively went to the bar where I believed he was and confronted him. In my distress, I made an ill-advised threat, mentioning the possibility of obtaining a gun. Although I never intended to harm anyone, I am aware that my words were alarming and distressing to those who overheard.

During this encounter, I did slap my boyfriend in the face, an action that I now realize was inappropriate and lacking in self-control. I deeply regret resorting to physical force, but I must emphasize that it was an isolated incident and no further harm was inflicted.

I would like to take this opportunity to address the court regarding some mitigating factors in my case. Firstly, I have no prior criminal record. This incident is entirely out of character for me and I assure the court that it will not be repeated. Furthermore, I have been actively seeking assistance in addressing my emotional well-being by attending therapy sessions once a week. This demonstrates my commitment to personal growth and my sincere desire to learn from my mistakes and become a more responsible member of society.

Your Honor, I humbly request leniency in sentencing, taking into consideration my guilty plea as a mitigating factor. I understand the seriousness of my actions and the impact they have had on others, and I am genuinely remorseful for the distress caused. I assure the court that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience, and I am committed to making amends and ensuring that such behavior is never repeated.

Thank you for your understanding, Your Honor.

